### Scaphoid

<Image
  src="https://anatomy.host.dartmouth.edu/HAE/Upperextremity/hand/radiology/scaphoid/scaphoid.jpg"
  alt="scaphoid-hand"
  wrap="right"
  size="md"
/>
This is a radiograph of the wrist with the hand in ulnar deviation (adduction). This "opens up" the scaphoid bone and decreases the amount of overlap with adjacent carpal bones. This view is very useful in evaluating for scaphoid bone fractures.

### Boxer's Fracture

A boxer's fracture typically involves the neck of the 5th metacarpal bone. In addition to any deformity seen from the angulation of the fracture, loss of the prominence of this "knuckle" when making a fist may be seen with this fracture.
