### MRI Axial Wrist

The following labled images show T2-weighted axial MRIs of the wrist. Image 1 is the most proximal and image 3 the most distal. The first image was taken at the distal forearm. Remember that by convention, cross sectional images are viewed as though you were standing at the foot of a supine patient, looking up towards their head. The top of the image is anterior and the bottom, posterior.

Connective tissue elements, such as tendons and ligaments will appear black in these images.

